<p>The sensitivity, specificity and accuracy of our method was calculated for both species assignment and genotyping. Sensitivity was computed by the formula 
 <inline-formula id="pntd.0007231.e001">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pntd.0007231.e001.jpg" id="pntd.0007231.e001g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M1">
    <mfrac>
     <mrow>
      <mi>T</mi>
      <mi>P</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi>T</mi>
      <mi>P</mi>
      <mo>+</mo>
      <mi>F</mi>
      <mi>N</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>, specificity by the formula 
 <inline-formula id="pntd.0007231.e002">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pntd.0007231.e002.jpg" id="pntd.0007231.e002g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M2">
    <mfrac>
     <mrow>
      <mi>T</mi>
      <mi>N</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi>T</mi>
      <mi>N</mi>
      <mo>+</mo>
      <mi>F</mi>
      <mi>P</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> and accuracy by the formula 
 <inline-formula id="pntd.0007231.e003">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pntd.0007231.e003.jpg" id="pntd.0007231.e003g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M3">
    <mfrac>
     <mrow>
      <mi>T</mi>
      <mi>P</mi>
      <mo>+</mo>
      <mi>T</mi>
      <mi>N</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi>T</mi>
      <mi>P</mi>
      <mo>+</mo>
      <mi>F</mi>
      <mi>P</mi>
      <mo>+</mo>
      <mi>F</mi>
      <mi>N</mi>
      <mo>+</mo>
      <mi>T</mi>
      <mi>N</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> [
 <xref rid="pntd.0007231.ref042" ref-type="bibr">42</xref>]. In these formulas: TP = True Positives, FP = False Positives, TN = True Negatives and FN = False Negatives.
</p>
